{"type":"text","timestamp":1775880878626,"sessionID":"ses_285413e5cffeJ1uMHvGw8waBPV","part":{"id":"prt_d7abfb8da0014MFth2U0cuj1Vl","messageID":"msg_d7abface8001SaH05gx0yBLA45","sessionID":"ses_285413e5cffeJ1uMHvGw8waBPV","type":"text","text":"Now I have a complete picture. Let me create the proposal.md file:","time":{"start":1775880878624,"end":1775880878624}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775880900660,"sessionID":"ses_285413e5cffeJ1uMHvGw8waBPV","part":{"id":"prt_d7abfba22001GZhNbDYfF5Z3V2","messageID":"msg_d7abface8001SaH05gx0yBLA45","sessionID":"ses_285413e5cffeJ1uMHvGw8waBPV","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_b65811af41204763b66d3d1a","state":{"status":"error","input":{"content":"# Unit Test Proposal for pkg/workloadmanager (AR-038)\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe purpose of this unit test effort is to increase test coverage for the `pkg/workloadmanager` module, which manages AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources in Kubernetes. This module is critical for sandbox lifecycle management, including creation, deletion, garbage collection, and cleanup of associated Kubernetes resources.\n\n## Scope\n\n### Existing Test Coverage\n\n| File | Test File | Coverage Status |\n|------|-----------|-----------------|\n| `types.go` | - | Partial (API response helpers in service_test.go) |\n| `service.go` | `service_test.go` | ~70% (CRUD operations tested, sandbox operations partially covered) |\n| `batch.go` | - | **0%** |\n| `cleanup.go` | - | **0%** |\n| `expiration.go` | `expiration_test.go` | Good (isExpired*, shouldExpire*, ExpirationChecker) |\n| `gc.go` | `gc_test.go` | Good (GCWorker lifecycle, expiration checks) |\n| `graceful.go` | `graceful_test.go` | Good (connection tracking, draining) |\n| `retry.go` | - | **0%** |\n| `events.go` | - | **0%** |\n| `server.go` | `server_test.go` | Partial (basic HTTP handlers) |\n| `client.go` | `client_test.go` | Good (client creation, path expansion) |\n| `reconciler/reconciler.go` | `reconciler_test.go` | Partial |\n\n### Components Requiring Additional Tests\n\n#### 1. `batch.go` - BatchManager\n- `handleDeleteAllSandboxes()`: async deletion threshold handling\n- `handleDeleteByLabelSelector()`: label-based deletion\n- `deleteStaleSandboxes()`: stale sandbox cleanup with concurrent deletion\n\n#### 2. `cleanup.go` - CleanupManager\n- `cleanupServices()`: service owner reference matching\n- `cleanupConfigMaps()`: configmap auto-delete annotation handling\n- `cleanupPVCs()`: PVC retain policy logic\n- `cleanupOrphanedResources()`: orchestration of cleanup operations\n- `CleanupAllResources()`: full resource cleanup\n- `FindOrphanedServices()`: orphaned service detection\n\n#### 3. `retry.go` - Retry Logic\n- `retryDeletion()`: retry with exponential backoff\n- `retryWithBackoff()`: configurable retry with backoff\n- `WithRetry()`: public retry wrapper\n- `IsTransientError()`: transient error detection (has bug: returns true prematurely)\n\n#### 4. `events.go` - EventRecorder\n- `emitDeletionEvent()`: Kubernetes event emission\n- `emitOrphanCleanupEvent()`, `emitTTLExpirationEvent()`, `emitIdleTimeoutEvent()`, `emitMaxLifetimeEvent()`, `emitStaleCleanupEvent()`: specific event types\n- `sendDeletionWebhook()`: webhook HTTP client with retry logic\n- `logDeletionAudit()`: audit logging\n- `LogDeletionComplete()`: completion logging\n\n#### 5. Additional Coverage for `service.go`\n- `DeleteSandbox()`: sandbox deletion by session ID\n- `GetSandboxBySessionID()`: sandbox lookup\n- `ListSandboxes()`: combined listing from both AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter\n- `sandboxFromAgentRuntime()`: conversion function\n- `sandboxFromCodeInterpreter()`: conversion function\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Benefits\n1. **Increased Reliability**: Comprehensive test coverage reduces regression risk for sandbox lifecycle operations\n2. **Bug Detection**: Tests for `IsTransientError()` will catch the existing bug (always returns true)\n3. **Safe Refactoring**: Batch deletion and cleanup operations can be safely modified with test coverage\n4. **Documentation**: Tests serve as executable documentation of expected behavior\n5. **CI Confidence**: Full test suite enables confident continuous integration\n\n### Risks\n1. **Fake Client Complexity**: Testing `cleanup.go` and `events.go` requires extensive fake k8s client setup\n2. **Timing Sensitivity**: `retry.go` tests involve timing-dependent behavior\n3. **HTTP Mocking**: `sendDeletionWebhook()` requires HTTP handler mocking\n\n### Estimated Test Files to Create/Enhance\n- `batch_test.go` (new, ~150 lines)\n- `cleanup_test.go` (new, ~200 lines)\n- `retry_test.go` (new, ~100 lines)\n- `events_test.go` (new, ~150 lines)\n- `service_test.go` (enhance, ~100 additional lines)\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### 1. Integration Tests with Real Kubernetes Cluster\n- **Pros**: Tests actual behavior, no fake setup needed\n- **Cons**: Requires cluster access, slower, harder to CI\n- **Verdict**: Not preferred for unit tests; focus on well-isolated unit tests\n\n### 2. Table-Driven Tests\n- **Pros**: Comprehensive edge case coverage, easy to extend\n- **Cons**: Can become verbose for complex scenarios\n- **Verdict**: Use for simple functions (retry, expiration)\n\n### 3. Property-Based Testing\n- **Pros**: Discovers edge cases automatically\n- **Cons**: Requires additional library (testing/quick), higher complexity\n- **Verdict**: Not needed for this module; deterministic tests suffice\n\n### 4. Mock Libraries (testify/mock, gomock)\n- **Pros**: Cleaner mock setup, verification methods\n- **Cons**: Additional dependency, learning curve\n- **Verdict**: Use manual fakes where possible (consistent with existing code)\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n1. **Phase 1**: `retry_test.go` - Simple, foundational\n2. **Phase 2**: `batch_test.go` - Uses existing WorkloadManager interface\n3. **Phase 3**: `cleanup_test.go` - Requires k8s fake client setup\n4. **Phase 4**: `events_test.go` - Requires k8s fake client and HTTP mocking\n5. **Phase 5**: Enhance `service_test.go` - Sandbox operation coverage\n\n## Conclusion\n\nThis test coverage effort targets the untested components in `pkg/workloadmanager` that handle critical sandbox lifecycle operations. The existing test infrastructure (fake clients in `service_test.go`) provides a foundation to build upon. The effort will significantly improve code quality and reduce regression risk for this size-L module.","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775880900650,"end":1775880900657}}}}
